## > test blocks, in revo

they let you keep small smoke tests next to the code they exercise
they only run when you pass `--test`
they fail only when you return an error

##
fn add(a, b) a + b

# the body sees the same module scope as the rest of the file
test "addition" do
	assert(add(20, 22) == 22)?
end

# `?` still works inside a test body, so result tuples stay the same
test "unwrap result tuples" do
	const value = (:ok, 10)?
	assert(value == 10)?
end

# when all expressions succeed, the block just falls through
test "truthy checks" do
	assert(len("hello") == 5)?
	4
end
